## VadrJSCore

Provides the core functionality for vadr analytics to platform 
specific SDKs such as AFrame, ReactVR.
Checks for default events that need to be generated at each frame.
Makes calls to generate default events.
Provides unix time of each frame begin to all modules.

## Logger

Used to control logging to console based on log level.
Log levels are: 0 - Log nothing, 1 - Only error, 2 - Till Warnings, 3 - till Info,
4 - Log everything including debug

### getLogLevel

Get log level for analytics

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** 

### setLogLevel

Set log level for analytics

**Parameters**

-   `level` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** Integer logLevel value between 0 and 4

### error

Log error

**Parameters**

-   `log` **arguments** arguments

### warn

Log warning

**Parameters**

-   `log` **arguments** arguments

### info

Log info

**Parameters**

-   `log` **arguments** arguments

### debug

Log debug messages

**Parameters**

-   `log` **arguments** arguments

## ApplicationConfig

Contains the application specific information such as App id, token, 
version, test mode, default information collection frequency etc.

### setApplication

Sets the application details such as appId, appToken, version

**Parameters**

-   `appId` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** application id provided by vadr
-   `token` **token** application token provided by vadr
-   `version` **version** version of application set by developer

### getApplicationConfig

Returns the application config set by user

Returns **[object](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object)** cloned version of application config dict

### setSdkType

Sets the SDK type used by the application. Set by the platform implementation

**Parameters**

-   `sdk` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** sdk type

### getSdkType

Returns the platform SDK is used for

Returns **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** sdkType

### setTestMode

Sets the test mode of the application

**Parameters**

-   `test` **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** set it to true while developing, false when shipping in 
    production

### getTestMode

Returns the test mode value

Returns **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** testMode

### getDataPostTimeInterval

Returns the time interval between send data request

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** 

### getMaxEventsNumber

Returns the max number of events after which a request is scheduled to the server

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)**

## TimeManager

Manages the different timings in the web application

### init

Init the time manager, sets frameUnixTime to current value

### tick

Updates the application timings.
Calculates frameTime as the difference of current 
frame time and the previous frame time. In case app was not active the previous frame,
sets the frame time to 0. Correspondingly calculates timeSinceStart and 
playTimeSinceStart

**Parameters**

-   `frameTime` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** specify the frameDuration if known [optional]

### setAppActive

toggle appActive flag

**Parameters**

-   `newState`  

### setRemoveHeadsetPausesPlay

toggle if removing headset pauses play time

**Parameters**

-   `newState` **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** true if play is to be paused on removing headset, else false

### setHeadsetState

toggle headset put on / removed

**Parameters**

-   `newState` **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** new headset state, true id put on, false if taken off

### reset

Reset the timings, sets the frame time to unix time provided, reset others

### getFrameUnixTime

Get the frameUnixTime

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** unixTime of the current frame

### getFrameDuration

Get the previous frame duration

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** duration of the previous frame in milliseconds

### getFrameDurationSeconds

Get the previous frame duration

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** duration of the previous frame in seconds

### getTimeSinceStart

Get time since start of application

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** 

### getPlayTimeSinceStart

Get actual play time since start

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** 

### getPlayTimeSinceStartSeconds

Get actual play time since start in seconds

Returns **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** 

### playVideo

Play the video, use to 1. create new video (assumes video duration was set to 
0 by the last video stop call) 2. play existing paused video.

### pauseVideo

Pause the currently playing video

### stopVideo

Stop the currently playing video. Resets the video duration to 0

### setVideoDuration

Set new seek positon of the currently playing video

**Parameters**

-   `newSeek`  

### getVideoState

Gets the video play state, true if playing, false if not playing or paused

### getVideoDuration

Get the current seek position of the playing video

## User

Stores the user information such as user id and other details such as 
age, gender etc.
Until userId id is set, device id is used in its place.

### setUserId

Set user id

**Parameters**

-   `newUserId` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** userId of the user
-   `override` **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** override any existing userId

### setExtraInfo

Used to set any extra user information such as age, gender etc.

**Parameters**

-   `infoKey` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** name of the paramter being set
-   `infoValue` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** value of the parameter

### getUserDictionary

Used to get all the user details in a dictionary format

Returns **dictionary** dictionary

## DataManager

Stores registered data, manages data requests to the server

### init

Init the collection of data

### addSessionExtra

Add extra information to the session

**Parameters**

-   `infoKey` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** key which identifies the information, max 50 characters
-   `infoValue`  

### addScene

create scene session

**Parameters**

-   `sceneId` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** id of the new scene
-   `sceneName` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** name of the new scene [optional]

### closeScene

close the ongoing scene

### addMedia

Adds media to the media list

**Parameters**

-   `mediaId` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** Developer defined mediaId for the media
-   `name` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** Media name to be displayed to the analytics user
-   `type` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** Type of media 1 - Video, 2 - Photo
-   `url` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** Url for the media [optional]

### closeMedia

Closes an ongoing media session

### getMediaState

Retuns the media state, true is media is playing, false if media is not playing

Returns **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** media state

### registerEvent

Adds event to event list of media if it exists, else to its own events list

**Parameters**

-   `eventName` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** name of the event
-   `position` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** 3D position associated with the event
-   `extra` **[object](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object)** extra information and filter key-value pairs in the event

## Session

Stores events for a single session

**Parameters**

-   `sessionToken`  
-   `startTime`  
-   `extra`  
-   `extras` **[object](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object)** dictionary containing extra information about the session 
    such as location, language, connection etc. User fields are fetched automatically

### setExtra

Set or overwrite any extra key value pair

**Parameters**

-   `key` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** 
-   `value`

## MediaSession

Stores events for a single media playback.

**Parameters**

-   `mediaId` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** Developer defined mediaId for the media
-   `name` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** Media name to be displayed to the analytics user
-   `type` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** Type of media 1 - Video, 2 - Photo
-   `sceneStartTime` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** Time since start of scene when media is displayed
-   `url` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** Url for the media [optional]

### setUrl

Assign url of media after initialization

**Parameters**

-   `newUrl` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** name of the property to be set

### registerEvent

Adds event to the events list

**Parameters**

-   `eventName` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** name of the event
-   `position` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** 3D position associated with the event
-   `extra` **[object](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object)** extra information and filter key-value pairs in the event
-   `gameTime` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** time since start of scene when the event occurred

### getDictionary

Fetch the dictionary corresponding to this media

Returns **[object](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object)** dictionary form of media

### getDuplicate

Returns a duplicate of the current media without any data in it

Returns **[MediaSession](#mediasession)** duplicate media session

## ServerRequestManager

Manages creating full request dictionaries, adding them to db, 
And retreving them to make post calls to server

### addDataRequest

Adds request to send data in list of requests

**Parameters**

-   `requestDict` **[object](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object)** The dictionary contaning data for the added request

## DataCollector

Manages the collection of default events

### setPositionCallback

Sets the function to call when setting position

**Parameters**

-   `positionFunction` **[function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** 

### setGazeCallback

Sets the function to call when calculating gaze hit point

**Parameters**

-   `gazeFunction` **[function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** 

### setAngleCallback

Sets the function to call when calculating gaze hit point

**Parameters**

-   `angleFunction` **[function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** 

### configureEventCollection

Configures which events to collect by default and by what frequency

**Parameters**

-   `eventType` **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** type of event - Orientation, Gaze, Performance
-   `collectionStatus` **[boolean](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean)** set to true if you want to collect the event
-   `timePeriod` **[number](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number)** time period in milliseconds after which to collect the data

### tick

Checks if any default data needs to be collected after each frame

### reset

Reset the last fetch time of all the events, used when timeManager resets

## OrientationCollector

Calculates the position and other events associated with position data

### setPositionCallback

Sets the position callback

**Parameters**

-   `newPositionCallback` **[function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** new callback to be used to fetch position

### getEvents

returns array of all the position related events with extra info and filters

Returns **[array](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array)** event deatails in format [name, position, extraInfo]

### getCurrentPosition

Fetch the position calculated in current frame.

Returns **[string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String)** currentPosition

### setAngleCallback

**Parameters**

-   `newAngleCallback`
